{
  "stem": "18470.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 234.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Teaching kids who don't-- who don't want--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--who don't want to learn.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "On a Sunday morning.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHTER] It's also very dangerous.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You get hit with spit balls and all sorts of things.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But that was an easier kind of integration to deal with than my parents had.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They never really caught their breath in this country.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, it was always there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Rabbi Silverstein, who was the rabbi of my synagogue in New York, thought that I should go to yeshiva, which I did for a while, Chaim Berlin.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But that was not for me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then I began to seriously look into the Jewish Theological Seminary, their evening school, and I ended up at the Jewish Institute of Religion in New York, which I was really at home in, because of its freedom of restrictions, encouragement of independent thought, and very brilliant people with great ideas trying to instruct us in all kinds of interesting subjects-- Jewish history, literature, Hebrew language, Bible.",
      "word_count": 68
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I loved it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was that simple.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was like I was a-- a duck in the right pond.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Hebrew Union doesn't admit you into rabbinic school until you have a bachelor's degree.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I went to night school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "HUC in New York had pre-rabbinic academy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So two nights a week I went to HUC at night.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I worked during the day, and went to college, and I lived on the subway, you know.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[SIGHS] That's how you get everything done.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I lived in Brooklyn.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My school was two trains to Boys High School every day, and then to Manhattan for the college, then back to home, and work in between.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I loved what I was doing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't know of any other way to do the things that I was doing.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
